name: Solarigrafia: Rovaniemi 2006
description:
This is a solargraph (solarigraph/solarigrafia), an image captured directly on photographic paper using a DIY pinhole camera. The image records the path of the sun over roughly two months in Rovaniemi, Finland.

Exposure: Early February, 2006 to April 7, 2006
Location: Rovaniemi, Finland (66.49870540840831, 25.734149027551734)

Time has destroyed the original. This digital version was scanned and processed on April 11, 2006.
